relation: References the physical hierarchy to which this cube column belongs. The hierarchy is contained in a sub-element called RefPhysicalHierarchy.
References the physical level to which this cube column belongs. The level is contained in a sub-element called RefPhysicalLevel.
textBeforeTable: Table 8-26 Cube Column Child Elements The cube column tag includes the following child elements: parentRef: References the parent of a dimension. genNumber: The column is the root member of the hierarchy. Called Root in the Administration Tool. levelNumber: The column is the lowest member of the hierarchy. Called Leaf in the Administration Tool. memberKey: The column is a member key. ancestorRef: References the ancestor of a dimension. none: The column does not have a property type. Note that this type is mapped to Member Alias in the Administration Tool. other: The type is different than those listed, or unknown. attribute: Attribute type, for attribute dimensions. memnor: Memnor type, used for outline sorts in the logical layer. Imported at the lowest level of each dimension. Called Outline Sort in the Administration Tool. uda: User Defined Attribute (UDA) type. For Essbase dimensional columns only. Indicates the property type of the cube column. Valid values are: dimPropType The time at which row counts were last updated for this cube column. lastUpdated The latest number of rows retrieved for this cube column.
